t_id":"c5bfac93-8575-4b9e-af4f-12feafa46881","description":"The Industrial Injuries Advisory Council (IIAC) is an independent scientific advisory body that looks at industrial injuries benefit and how it is administered. IIAC is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Work and Pensions .","document_type":"organisation","locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Industrial Injuries Advisory Council","withdrawn":false,"details":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Industrial Injuries Advisory Council"},"brand":"department-for-work-pensions","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/121/s300_short-guides-landing4.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/121/s960_short-guides-landing4.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/industrial-injuries-advisory-council","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/industrial-injuries-advisory-council"}],"primary_publishing_organisation":[{"analytics_identifier":"PB231","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/industrial-injuries-advisory-council","base_path":"/government/organisations/industrial-injuries-advisory-council","content_id":"c5bfac93-8575-4b9e-af4f-12feafa46881","description":"The Industrial Injuries Advisory Council (IIAC) is an independent scientific advisory body that looks at industrial injuries benefit and how it is administered. IIAC is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Department for Work and Pensions .","document_type":"organisation","locale":"en","schema_name":"organisation","title":"Industrial Injuries Advisory Council","withdrawn":false,"details":{"logo":{"formatted_title":"Industrial Injuries Advisory Council"},"brand":"department-for-work-pensions","default_news_image":{"url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/121/s300_short-guides-landing4.jpg","high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/default_news_organisation_image_data/file/121/s960_short-guides-landing4.jpg"}},"links":{},"api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/industrial-injuries-advisory-council","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/industrial-injuries-advisory-council"}],"available_translations":[{"title":"Invitation to an IIAC meeting on 11 July 2019","public_updated_at":"2019-05-01T13:18:05Z","document_type":"news_story","schema_name":"news_article","base_path":"/government/news/invitation-to-an-iiac-meeting-on-11-july-2019","description":"An opportunity for members of the public to learn about the work of the Industrial Injuries Advisory Council (IIAC).","api_path":"/api/content/government/news/invitation-to-an-iiac-meeting-on-11-july-2019","withdrawn":false,"content_id":"e515ebc4-cf14-4f3a-ace7-95705f94c59e","locale":"en","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/news/invitation-to-an-iiac-meeting-on-11-july-2019","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/invitation-to-an-iiac-meeting-on-11-july-2019","links":{}}]},"description":"An opportunity for members of the public to learn about the work of the Industrial Injuries Advisory Council (IIAC).","details":{"body":"<p>The aim of the meeting is to give members of the public, their representatives, and people with a professional interest in occupational diseases, the opportunity to learn and ask questions about the council’s work.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting will take place in Leeds from 10am to 3:15pm at:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nHilton Leeds City\n<br>Neville Street\n<br>Leeds\n<br>LS1 4BX\n<br>\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>The meeting will include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>an explanation of the council’s role in making recommendations to ministers about the industrial injuries scheme</li>\n  <li>presentations and discussions about the council’s work in the past year</li>\n  <li>an opportunity to contribute views and ideas on the council’s future work</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The council welcomes any questions in advance of the meeting, where they will respond.</p>\n\n<div class=\"call-to-action\">\n<p>Reserve a place or ask your questions by Thursday 27 June 2019 at <a href=\"mailto:iiac@dwp.gov.uk\">iiac@dwp.gov.uk</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>It might not be possible to accept all applications if the number of requests is higher than expected.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"about-iiac\">About <abbr title=\"Industrial Injuries Advisory Council\">IIAC</abbr>\n</h2>\n\n<p>The Industrial Injuries Advisory Council (<abbr title=\"Industrial Injuries Advisory Council\">IIAC</abbr>) provides advice to the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions and the Department for Communities in Northern Ireland on matters relating to the industrial injuries scheme. In particular, they give advice on which diseases, and the jobs that cause them, should be included in the scheme.</p>\n\n<p>The council is formed of medical, scientific and legal experts, and representatives of employers and employed earners.</p>\n\n<p>The council does not represent the Department for Work and Pensions and has no involvement in individual claims or decisions.</p>\n\n","change_history":[{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2019-05-01T12:55:57.989Z"}]},"document_status":"published_but_needs_2i","created_by":"Nungshi Malik","last_updated_by":"Nungshi Malik","political":false,"government":{"title":"2015 Conservative government","slug":"2015-conservative-government","start_date":"2015-05-07T23:00:00.000Z","end_date":"","current":true}}